&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Senior Specialist Nurse – Chronic Pain Management Service&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full-time (37.5 hrs)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity for a Band 7 Senior Specialist Nurse to join the Chronic Pain Management Service at Ashford &amp; St Peters’ Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. Our multidisciplinary service works together to improve the quality of life of people suffering with persistent pain. Our team is comprised of Consultants in Pain Management, Specialist Nurses, Clinical Psychologists, Senior Physiotherapists, Extended Scope Practitioners and Secretarial support. Using a biopsychosocial model of care we provide a variety of treatments and pain management approaches to our patients which supports them to manage and live well with their chronic pain conditions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the Senior Specialist Nurse, supported by the Matron to the service and the Consultant Lead, you will manage, guide and support the nursing team in the day to day delivery of expert care within our outpatient pain management service. Utilising your leadership, advanced nursing skills and pain knowledge to enable you to provide Nurse-led Clinics, delivery of nursing input into Pain Management Programmes and be responsible for the patient Advice Line. The post holder will also provide specialist pain advice and education to other health care professionals within and outside the Trust and work closely with the Trust’s Inpatient Pain Service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have extensive experience of working within a pain management service and of leading a team in the delivery of expert care. A passion for pain management and a desire to develop the service and the team is required. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Kelly Irvine Matron Diagnostics, Therapies, Trauma Orthopaedics and iMSK services 01932723635 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;kellyirvine1@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
